# FoodLens Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- Prisma ORM (client at `@/generated/prisma/client`)
- Vercel AI SDK with pluggable providers (Google Gemini / OpenAI / Anthropic / Mistral)

## Code Conventions
- Use Chinese for user-facing strings (UI text, AI prompts, error messages)
- Use English for code identifiers, comments, and technical documentation
- Always use `@/` import alias for project files
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- Prefer Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed
- Use Zod for all API input/output validation

## File Organization
- `src/app/` — Pages and API routes (App Router)
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui primitives (do not edit)
- `src/components/` — Custom business components
- `src/lib/` — Utilities, clients, shared logic
- `src/hooks/` — Custom React hooks
- `prisma/` — Database schema

## Key Files
- `src/lib/ai.ts` — AI provider abstraction (getModel, getAvailableProviders)
- `src/lib/prisma.ts` — Prisma singleton client
- `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` — Browser Supabase client
- `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` — Server Supabase client
- `src/lib/schema.ts` — Zod schemas for scan results

## Database
- Always use Prisma for DB operations, not raw Supabase queries
- Supabase is used for Auth and Storage only
- Run `npx prisma generate` after schema changes

## AI Integration
- Use `getModel()` from `@/lib/ai.ts` — never import provider SDKs directly in routes
- Use `generateObject` with Zod schema for structured output
- Store `aiProvider` field in Scan records for traceability
